==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Montanist
<hw>Mon"ta*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of <persfn>Mintanus</persfn>, a Phrygian
enthusiast of the second century, who claimed that the Holy Spirit, the
Paraclete, dwelt in him, and employed him as an instrument for purifying
and guiding men in the Christian life.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mon`ta*nis"tic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<wf>Mon`ta*nis"tic*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Montant</ent>⟦br⟧
